Djokovic made a strong start to their rain-delayed meeting on Friday, breaking serve twice to clinch the opening set but struggled through the early rallies in the second set, winning just six points in the first four games. Nearly down 0-5, Djokovic got on the board but Prizmic served out the second set and claimed a decisive break in the fifth game of the third.Djokovic gamely served to stay in the match at 5-3, but Prizmic would not be denied and, with one last ace, clinched the biggest win of his young career—and matched his best result at a Masters 1000 event—in just over two hours.Awaiting him in the third round will be either No. 31 seed Ugo Humbert or Czechia's Vit Kopriva, who reached the fourth round last week in Madrid.

