The decision to sell came after the reality stars publicly ended their nine-year relationship in 2023, after Sandoval's affair with their “Vanderpump Rules” co-star Raquel Leviss was exposed.

The music artist originally attempted to keep Madix from selling the house. In January 2024, the Bravolebrity appeared on an episode of the “Viall Files” podcast where he claimed he made his ex an all-cash offer of $3.1 million to buy the home. 

However, Madix turned him down. Instead, she took him to court and sued him to force the sale of the house so they could split the proceeds.

Advertisement

At the time, the “Love Island” host said in a February 2024 episode of “Vanderpump Rules” that she didn't want to sell to Sandoval because he “broke the home.”

“He f–ked all of this up. He doesn't get to do that and then just keep it,” Madix said in a confessional. 

Sandoval countered Madix's comments, saying that Madix didn't pay the bills on their home for months.



